
USE R WITH JUPYTER-NOTEBOOK IN BROWSER

1. launch anaconda-navigator
2. select 'home'
        switch to python3
3. select 'Environments'
        'EnvDataSci'
   if envrionment does not exist, then create it with R
4. Launch a terminal from the environments window, after selecting (activating) 
the appropriate environment. Then launch Jupyter from the command line.

https://docs.anaconda.com/anaconda/navigator/tutorials/r-lang/

USE R WITH JUPYTER-NOTEBOOK IN BROWSER

To convert ipynb to Rmd, then download as md from jupyter-notebook in browser.

1. Rename file as .Rmd 

2. Then for each R cell convert

'''R

'''

to 

'''{R}

'''

